  "prompt": "I love her a lot but her past troubles me and I don't trust her. Please read comment. What should I do?",
  "response": "It's understandable to feel troubled by a partner's past, especially if it affects your trust in the relationship. Here are some steps you can consider to navigate this situation:\n\n1. **Reflect on Your Feelings**: Take some time to understand why her past troubles you. Are these feelings based on the reality of her actions or on assumptions? Understanding your emotions can help you address them more clearly.\n\n2. **Open Communication**: Have an honest and calm conversation with her about your feelings. Share your concerns without placing blame. It\u2019s important to listen to her side of the story as well, which can provide context and might alleviate some of your worries.\n\n3. **Building Trust**: Trust takes time to develop. Consider what actions both of you can take to build trust in your relationship. This might include setting boundaries or finding ways to reassure each other.\n\n4. **Assess the Relationship**: Evaluate if your love for her outweighs the concerns you have. If the past is having a significant impact on your happiness and the future of the relationship, it may be worth considering whether it is a healthy situation for both of you.\n\n5. **Seek Professional Help**: Sometimes talking to a therapist or counselor (either individually or as a couple) can provide valuable insights and strategies to work through trust issues.\n\n6. **Decide What\u2019s Best for You**: Ultimately, it\u2019s important to prioritize your own well-being. If you feel that the past will continue to negatively impact your relationship, it may be necessary to consider whether this relationship is right for you in the long term.\n\nTrust your instincts and take the time you need to make the right decision for yourself.",
